<HEADLINE>
<P>
RABBI MARSHALL T. MEYER; LEADER OF JEWISH LIBERALISM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rabbi Marshall T. Meyer, 63, a leading voice of American Jewish 
liberalism.Eight years ago Meyer founded Tikkun, a liberal journal that has 
become one of the most widely read Jewish periodicals in the country. Meyer 
lived for 25 years in Argentina, where he founded what is now the largest 
Jewish congregation in Buenos Aires. In 1962, he began the first rabbinical 
seminary in South America. Meyer was also a forceful critic of the military 
dictatorship that seized power in Argentina in 1976, and he and his family were 
harassed and threatened. In 1985, Meyer assumed the pulpit of Congregation 
B'nai Jeshurun in New York City. In Manhattan on Wednesday of cancer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
