IT'D BE A REAL KICK TO GET MORE SOCCER COVERAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The L.A. Times' coverage of high school soccer is virtually nonexistent.There 
have been several major tournaments in this area during the past two weeks. No 
stories in my edition. The Day in Sports, however, does give me the indoor 
track schedule (I know the Knights of Columbus Indoor Games will take place in 
Saskatoon next month), the winners of the Russian Skating Championships 
(congratulations Anzhelka Krylova-Vladimir Fyodorov), and the complete NFL log. 
Thanks fellas, you're doing a great job. 
</P>
<P>
