<HEADLINE>
<P>
SALARY CAP? HOW ABOUT A CELEBRATION CAP? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 This is an open letter to all players in the NFL. 
</P>
<P>
 There seems to be too many multimillion-dollar, egotistical yahoos determined 
to transform football stadiums into three-ring circuses. As a football player 
it's your job to sack the quarterback, catch 40-yard touchdown passes and block 
potential game-winning field goals. Don't worry, we know who you guys are 
without you jumping up and down like a bunch of screaming banshees! 
</P>
<P>
 Please save your celebrating for the appropriate time, after the game. 
</P>
<P>
 GREGORY K. THOMAS 
</P>
<P>
 Encino 
</P>
