<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASKETBALL / COAST HOLIDAY CLASSIC; HUNTINGTON BEACH HOLDS OFF NEWPORT 
HARBOR, WINS TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM BIRSCHBACH, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After surviving five Newport Harbor rallies, Huntington Beach pulled away down 
the stretch to beat the Sailors, 78-73, in the championship game of the Coast 
Holiday Classic Friday night at Estancia High School. 
</P>
<P>
 With tournament MVP Tony Gonzalez on the bench after drawing his fifth foul 
and a 73-70 lead with 47 seconds remaining, Huntington Beach (6-6) got some 
clutch free-throw shooting from Josh Holland and Vasili Hatzirias, who hit two 
with 35 seconds remaining for a 76-70 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach had leads of eight, nine and 10 points four times only to see 
the Sailors come fighting back. 
</P>
<P>
 "I knew it would be that type of game," Huntington Beach Coach Roy Miller 
said. "They have a number of weapons. You think you're comfortable and someone 
hits a 22-footer and they're back in it." 
</P>
<P>
 Gonzalez contributed 30 points, eight rebounds and five assists, but he got in 
trouble when he lost his cool after being called for his third foul and drawing 
a technical with 1:34 remaining. Newport's Paul Tayyar, who had just hit a 
three-point basket, hit both free throws to narrow the Sailors' deficit to 
70-68. 
</P>
<P>
 Hatzirias, who had 16 points and four assists, hit a free throw with 1:18 
remaining and Matt Jones hit both ends of a one-and-one with 57 seconds left 
for a 73-68 lead before Gonzalez fouled out and center Ramy Shoukry made two 
free throws. 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor (7-5) was led in scoring by Danny Pulido with 23 points and 
Tayyar with 18 points, including three three-point field goals. Matt Malmquist 
added 13 points for Huntington Beach, which is 5-3 since Gonzalez rejoined team 
after the football playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 In the third-place game: 
</P>
<P>
 Edison 54, Long Beach Jordan 51 -- Micah Kroeger scored 23 points for Edison 
(7-1). Edison led, 17-6, after one quarter but the teams were tied, 26-26, at 
the half. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 In the fifth-place game: 
</P>
<P>
 Estancia 60, Corona del Mar 59 -- Estancia led, 59-51, with a minute left and 
hung on. Corona del Mar's Dan MacMillan made a three-pointer as time ran out to 
make it a one-point game. 
</P>
<P>
 Mark Pierson had 17 points and Clay Frenz added 15 for Estancia (7-7). Frenz, 
a senior guard, scored 11 points in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 MacMillan had 10 of his 12 points in the fourth quarter for Corona del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 In the seventh-place game: 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine 64, Santa Maria Righetti 53 -- Greg Foster scored a game-high 23 points 
for Irvine (4-7), the defending tournament champion. Foster showed balance in 
the entire game, scoring six in the first quarter, five each in the second and 
third and seven in the forth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 In the consolation championship: 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills 56, Napa Vintage 54 (OT) -- Donald Myers (six points) of Dana Hills 
scored the only basket of overtime. Dana Hills led, 27-26, at the half but 
needed a strong second half from Bob Hefty, a senior forward, to reach 
overtime. 
</P>
