<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; ANDERSON'S SHOOTING LEADS SCC PAST EVANGEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Todd Anderson made all seven shots he took from the field and finished with 20 
points to help Southern California College to a 95-82 victory over Evangel 
(Mo.) College in a men's basketball game Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Anderson also made six of eight free-throw attempts. Darren Thomas made four 
of five shots from the field and Court Bickmore made four of six for Southern 
California College, which shot 59% (33 for 56). 
</P>
<P>
 Thomas had 13 points and Bickmore 12 for SCC, which made 20 of 27 shots in the 
second half. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 In a nonconference women's game: 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California College 59, Evangel (Mo.) College 47 -- Emily Wedel scored 
17 points for Southern California College (10-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Nicole Kelley had 14 points and 13 rebounds and Jamie Zitterkopf added 10 
points and 10 rebounds for SCC. 
</P>
