<P>
AIR CANADA AGREES TO STOP SERVING PATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Air Canada has agreed to stop serving French pate to its first-class 
passengers, and an animal rights group claimed victory for the ban. 
</P>
<P>
 Pate de foie gras is produced by force-feeding ducks and geese to expand their 
livers. 
</P>
<P>
 Many birds die as a result, said the Washington-based animal rights group 
People for Ethical Treatment of Animals, which has urged major airlines to stop 
serving pate. 
</P>
<P>
 The Montreal-based airline has agreed to ban the delicacy on its flights 
starting in May, PETA spokesman Dan Matthews said. 
</P>
<P>
 Air Canada officials confirmed the decision on Friday but did not provide 
details on why it was made. 
