<P>
THE MOTHER OF ALL LISTS OF MISUSED WORDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Words and phrases such as politically correct , mother of all . . . and 
dysfunctional ought to be banished, says a list compiled annually by Lake 
Superior State University. 
</P>
<P>
 Since 1976, the school has accepted nominations for its unofficial "List of 
Words Banished From the Queen's English for Misuse, Overuse, or General 
Uselessness." 
</P>
<P>
 Among the 29 words and phrases recommended for banishment are dysfunctional 
(whose family isn't?) and mother of all . . . (translated from Arabic and worn 
out). 
</P>
<P>
 Politically correct came under fire, on the widespread belief that politicians 
are so often wrong. 
</P>
