<P>
MAN HELD IN GRANDDAUGHTER'S ABDUCTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 9-year-old girl was on her way back to Washington state by airline Friday 
night and her grandfather, a cleric, was in jail on suspicion of kidnaping 
after he was arrested in Cerritos. 
</P>
<P>
 Kitsap County, Wash., authorities said the grandfather, Frederick Aylward, 
took the girl on a church errand Wednesday, then faked an auto accident.The 
pair drove down the coast in rental cars until they checked into a Cerritos 
hotel, where Los Angeles County sheriff's deputies arrested Aylward on Friday 
and took the girl to the airport. 
</P>
<P>
 Lt. Jim Valdez of the Lakewood sheriff's station said the girl was "fine, just 
a little tired and scared and wants to go home." 
</P>
<P>
 Aylward, 51, is pastor of St. Mary's Orthodox Catholic Church, Kitsap County 
Sheriff Pat Jones said. He said family members told him that Aylward had a 
fascination with his granddaughter. 
</P>
<P>
 Jones said Aylward had been charged with kidnaping in 1978 when he disappeared 
for several months with his then-wife's 12-year old daughter, but the charges 
were dropped. 
</P>
