<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFF THE TICKER: MR. AND MRS. SECOND-RICHEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LESLIE HELM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Microsoft Corp.'s billionaire Chairman Bill Gates reportedly will marry 
fiancee Melinda French today on the Hawaiian island of Lanai. 
</P>
<P>
 Among the guests will be investor Warren Buffett, the only man in America 
richer than Gates.The Microsoft co-founder is worth an estimated $7 billion. 
</P>
<P>
 Microsoft competitors have expressed hope that the sultan of software will 
slow his pace to spend time with his wife. But Gates told a reporter that 
marriage will give him more time for work by eliminating the distractions of 
dating. 
</P>
<P>
 Gates, 38, met French, in her late 20s, shortly after she joined Microsoft in 
1987. Soon after their engagement was announced in March, the electronic mail 
was flying. Asked one message: "But does she do Windows?" LESLIE HELM 
</P>
</TEXT>
