<TEXT>
<P>
 Steel Companies, Union Issue Dumping Charges: Five U.S. steel bar producers 
and the United Steelworkers of America asked the government to impose 
anti-dumping duties on exporters in Brazil, India, Italy, Japan and Spain.A 
petition filed with the Commerce Department and the International Trade 
Commission said stainless steel bar from those countries is being sold in the 
United States at less than fair value. The five countries accounted for about 
65% of total stainless steel bar imports in 1993, said a written statement 
released by the U.S. companies and their union. Steel companies in those 
countries are probably being motivated by recessions in their home markets, the 
statement said. 
