<TEXT>
<P>
 Merrill Lynch Is Year's Top Underwriter: Merrill Lynch & Co. raised $174 
billion overall for financings that accounted for a 16.4% market share, 
Securities Data Corp. said.Goldman, Sachs & Co. finished second, raising $127 
billion for a 12% market share, and Lehman Bros. was third, booking $116 
billion for a 10.9% share of U.S. financings. Underwriting fees in 1993 
increased 34% over the $6.8 billion collected in 1992's record-breaking period. 
Domestic debt issuance set an all-time high of $433 billion in 1993, sparked by 
historically low interest rates. Investment-grade corporate debt totaled $378 
billion, 37% higher than in 1992. 
</P>
