<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHRISTMAS TREE SPARKS $150,000 OJAI HOUSE FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A house on Creek Road south of Ojai was gutted by fire on New Year's Eve, 
authorities said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The cause of the fire was still being investigated.It was sparked by a 
Christmas tree that caught fire, Ventura County fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 No one was injured in the blaze, which was called in to the Fire Department at 
about 4 p.m. after 17-year-old Eileen Friedlander found the family room in 
flames. 
</P>
<P>
 "I had just taken a bath and heard a weird noise, so I went to the door and 
saw smoke coming through the top of the door," said Eileen, who lives in the 
house with her parents and 13-year-old brother. "I opened the door and the 
family room was completely engulfed in flames." 
</P>
<P>
 Eileen escaped the flames unhurt. Her brother Brent was outside playing 
basketball. Their parents are vacationing in the Napa Valley and are due home 
Sunday, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire was contained at about 5:10 p.m. Authorities estimated it caused 
about $150,000 worth of damage to the three-bedroom, one-story house. 
</P>
</TEXT>
