<P>
BODY FOUND NEAR MOORPARK IS THAT OF FORMER CYPRESS RESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The body of a woman who was strangled and then dumped in a remote area near 
Moorpark has been identified as 20-year-old Mika C. Bissett, a former Cypress 
resident. 
</P>
<P>
 Michael Dubov, who was staying with Bissett, has confessed to strangling her 
Dec. 14 in Bissett's Venice apartment, Los Angeles Police Lt. John Rogers said. 
</P>
<P>
 Dubov has been booked into jail in Los Angeles on suspicion of murder and is 
being held on $1 million bail. 
</P>
<P>
 Rogers said Dubov waited several days after he strangled her, then drove the 
body to Ventura County and dumped it on a brush-covered embankment along a dirt 
road off Gabbert Road. 
</P>
<P>
 Dubov had reported Bissett missing Dec. 20, Rogers said. During an interview 
with detectives on Wednesday, Dubov confessed to the killing and led detectives 
to the body. 
</P>
<P>
 Rogers said Bissett was a student whose mother lives in Orange County. 
According to voter registration records, the young woman had lived in Cypress 
with her parents as recently as 1992. 
</P>
