<HEADLINE>
<P>
FACES '94: SOME NAMES TO BE RECKONED WITH IN THE NEW YEAR; MUSIC; DEAN COREY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS PASLES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The O.C. Philharmonic Society's new executive director has been called a team 
player with a good sense of humor and clever fund-raising ideas. He needs all 
that to lead the county'soldest and most prestigious music organization. 
</P>
<P>
 Formerly the San Diego Symphony's development director, Corey, 46, aims to 
continue the society's presentations of renowned orchestras and chamber 
ensembles, to help build a strong financial base and to negotiate a more open 
artistic policy regarding world music and dance presentations at the O.C. 
Performing Arts Center. Still commuting from San Diego, Corey plans to move 
with his family to O.C. soon. 
</P>
<P>
