<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND TV; ROSE PARADE COVERAGE FLOWERS ON 12 STATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The New Year begins today with the splendor of the Rose Parade and the 
excitement of the Rose Bowl game from Pasadena. 
</P>
<P>
 The "Tournament of Roses Parade" begins at 8 a.m. on CBS (Channels 2 and 8), 
NBC (4, 36 and 39), ABC (7, 3, 10 and 42), KTLA-TV Channel 5, KTTV-TV Channel 
11 and KMEX-TV Channel 34. 
</P>
<P>
 Actor William Shatner will ride as Grand Marshal and "Fantastic Adventure" is 
the theme of the 105th trek down Colorado Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
 KTLA will repeat the pageantry at 10:30 a.m., 1, 5 and 7:30 p.m. while Channel 
11 will offer a second live broadcast at 10:30 a.m. followed by repeats at 
12:30 and 3:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rose Bowl matches UCLA against Big Ten champion Wisconsin, which is making 
its first appearance in Pasadena in 31 years. Kickoff is set for 1:30 p.m. on 
ABC. 
</P>
<P>
 Other bowl telecasts include an NBC triple-header starting with the Fiesta 
Bowl (Arizona vs. Miami, Fla.) at 10 a.m.; the Cotton Bowl (Texas A&M vs. Notre 
Dame) at 1:30 p.m. and the Orange Bowl (Nebraska vs. Florida State) for the 
national championship at 5 p.m. ABC will carry the Sugar Bowl (Florida vs. West 
Virginia) at 5:30 p.m. 
</P>
