<HEADLINE>
<P>
KABC-TV GETS 'GOOD NEIGHBOR AWARD' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Television station KABC Channel 7 received the "Good Neighbor Award" from the 
Los Angeles Chapter of the American Red Cross for its financial support and 
co-sponsorship of the annual Kids Care Fair. 
</P>
<P>
 The station is credited with providing health care information to 
approximately 81,000 families, many of whom do not have access to regular 
health screenings or health care. 
</P>
<P>
 News anchor Steve Wolford and public affairs director Teresa Samaniego 
accepted the award on behalf of the station. 
</P>
</TEXT>
